# random-ai-prompt -- version (single source of truth).
#
# Format: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH[-prerelease]   (Semantic Versioning 2.0.0)
#
# This file is the canonical version string. Keep `package.json`'s "version"
# field in sync with it (the AI assistant does both in the same commit). Lines
# starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored; the first remaining line is the
# version.
#
# How to bump (see notes/reference/versioning.md for the full guide):
#   - PATCH (2.0.0 -> 2.0.1 -> ...): THE DEFAULT. Almost every change -- fixes
#     AND ordinary features. The PATCH number is not capped at 9.
#   - MINOR (2.0.x -> 2.1.0): a notable feature set / milestone.
#   - MAJOR (2.x -> 3.0.0): a breaking change or stability promise. The project
#     leader's call (junebug12851) -- never bumped automatically.
#
# 2.0.0 marks the June 2026 modernization: the whole codebase moved from
# CommonJS to ES modules, the toolchain moved to Node 24 LTS, and every
# dependency was taken to its current major (Express 5, yargs 18, open 11,
# node-fetch dropped for the built-in fetch). That is a breaking jump for anyone
# running an old Node, hence the MAJOR bump.
2.7.24